Zoe M💫rales Ervolino

ABOUT ART CONTACT ARCHIVE

Zoe Morales Ervolino is a New Yorker of Italian- and Colombian-American descent, and recent graduate of Yale University where she double-majored in American Studies (Visual, Audio, Literary, & Performance Cultures) and History (concentrating in Latin America).

Her thesis in American Studies, MISS-TIZAJE, took on the complex and absurd subject of Colombian beauty pageants.

Zoe has crafted, directed, and performed in artistic projects of all stripes and has experience working in the arts through her tenure with The Ford over the summer of 2020.

Since graduating, Zoe has worked for brands like Ceremonia and had her writing published in Mixed Mag.

Zoe resides in NYC.
